text: <TITLE_START> Membre dAgneau a la Judaique<TITLE_END><INGR_START> one 3-pound top-round or shoulder roast of lamb, without the bone<INGR_NEXT> salt and freshly ground pepper to taste<INGR_NEXT> 3 anchovy fillets, cut into 3 pieces each<INGR_NEXT> 6 cloves garlic, peeled and cut into slivers<INGR_NEXT> 3 sprigs fresh rosemary, or 1 teaspoon dried rosemary<INGR_NEXT> 3 sprigs fresh thyme, or 1 teaspoon dried thyme<INGR_NEXT> 3 sprigs fresh sage, or 1 teaspoon dried sage<INGR_NEXT> 8 small potatoes<INGR_NEXT> 1 pound green beans or zucchini, cut into chunks<INGR_NEXT> 2 tablespoons olive oil<INGR_NEXT> juice and grated peel of 1 orange<INGR_END><INSTR_START> preheat the oven to 450 degrees, and season the roast with salt and pepper.<INSTR_NEXT> then pierce the lamb with a sharp knife, and insert the anchovy fillets and the garlic bits in the slits.<INSTR_NEXT> place in a small roasting pan with the herbs and about a cup of water.<INSTR_NEXT> scatter the potatoes and the green beans or zucchini around the lamb, and toss the vegetables with a little olive oil.<INSTR_NEXT> place in the oven, and roast for 20 minutes.<INSTR_NEXT> then turn the oven down to 350 degrees, and continue cooking for about another 1 1/2 hours, or until done and a meat thermometer measures 140 degrees, basting occasionally.<INSTR_NEXT> remove the lamb from the oven and the pan.<INSTR_NEXT> add the orange juice and grated peel.<INSTR_NEXT> then cook, stirring, until the juices are reduced by about a half.<INSTR_NEXT> degrease the sauce, sprinkle with pepper, adjust seasonings, and serve.<INSTR_END>
title: Membre dAgneau a la Judaique
ingredients:
['One 3-pound top-round or shoulder roast of lamb, without the bone'
 'Salt and freshly ground pepper to taste'
 '3 anchovy fillets, cut into 3 pieces each'
 '6 cloves garlic, peeled and cut into slivers'
 '3 sprigs fresh rosemary, or 1 teaspoon dried rosemary'
 '3 sprigs fresh thyme, or 1 teaspoon dried thyme'
 '3 sprigs fresh sage, or 1 teaspoon dried sage' '8 small potatoes'
 '1 pound green beans or zucchini, cut into chunks'
 '2 tablespoons olive oil' 'Juice and grated peel of 1 orange']
instructions:
['Preheat the oven to 450 degrees, and season the roast with salt and pepper.'
 'Then pierce the lamb with a sharp knife, and insert the anchovy fillets and the garlic bits in the slits.'
 'Place in a small roasting pan with the herbs and about a cup of water.'
 'Scatter the potatoes and the green beans or zucchini around the lamb, and toss the vegetables with a little olive oil.'
 'Place in the oven, and roast for 20 minutes.'
 'Then turn the oven down to 350 degrees, and continue cooking for about another 1 1/2 hours, or until done and a meat thermometer measures 140 degrees, basting occasionally.'
 'Remove the lamb from the oven and the pan.'
 'Add the orange juice and grated peel.'
 'Then cook, stirring, until the juices are reduced by about a half.'
 'Degrease the sauce, sprinkle with pepper, adjust seasonings, and serve.']
instructions_v1:
['Add the orange juice and grated peel.'
 'Scatter the potatoes and the green beans or zucchini around the lamb, and toss the vegetables with a little olive oil.'
 'Place in a small roasting pan with the herbs and about a cup of water.'
 'Then cook, stirring, until the juices are reduced by about a half.'
 'Then turn the oven down to 350 degrees, and continue cooking for about another 1 1/2 hours, or until done and a meat thermometer measures 140 degrees, basting occasionally.'
 'Remove the lamb from the oven and the pan.'
 'Degrease the sauce, sprinkle with pepper, adjust seasonings, and serve.'
 'Place in the oven, and roast for 20 minutes.'

title: Simple Maple Baked Oatmeal
ingredients:
['3 cups quick-cooking oatmeal' '12 cup maple syrup' '1 cup water'
 '3 tablespoons heavy cream' '14 cup unsalted butter, melted' '2 eggs'
 '2 teaspoons baking powder' '1 teaspoon salt'
 '1 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice']
instructions:
['Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.'
 'Pour into greased 9x13" baking dish and spread evenly.'
 'Bake at 375 for 20 minutes, or until firm.'
 'Serve warm with milk or cream on top for a softer oatmeal, or store in the refrigerator and eat as a quick snack or breakfast bar.']

title: Cauliflower Cheese Soup
ingredients:
['2 tablespoons butter' '1 tablespoon olive oil'
 '2 cups cauliflower, flowerettes' '12 cup frozen hash brown potatoes'
 '1 12 cups chicken stock' '1 12 cups skim milk'
 '12 cup sharp cheddar cheese, shredded' '12 teaspoon salt'
 '14 teaspoon pepper']
instructions:
['Melt the butter and olive oil together in a saucepan.'
 'Add the onion and frozen hash browns and saute gently for 10 minutes.'
 'Stir in the chicken stock and bring to a boil.'
 'Add the cauliflower flowerettes, then lower the heat, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes.'
 'Take pan off the heat and either pour into a blender or food processor or easier than that, use a stick blender to roughly puree.'
 'Add mixture back to the saucepan and add the skim milk while off the heat.'
 'Add the shredded cheese and gently heat until simmering.'
 'Add salt and pepper to taste.']

title: Hummus (Home-Made)
ingredients:
['1 cup chickpeas dry' '5 cups water' '6 each bay leaves'
 '3/4 cup onions chopped' '1 clove garlic' '23 cup tomato puree'
 '2 tablespoons lemon juice' '3/4 teaspoon cumin ground'
 '1/4 teaspoon paprika' '18 teaspoon cayenne pepper'
 '1/4 teaspoon black pepper' '3/4 teaspoon salt']
instructions:
['Sort and rinse the chick-peas, then soak overnight in water.'
 'Drain them, then add 5 cups of water and bay leaves.'
 'Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for approximately 1 1/2 hours, or until the beans are completely soft.'
 'When cooked, drain the beans and puree until completely smooth in a food processor with the rest of the ingredients.']

title: Toasted Bread and Bittersweet Chocolate
ingredients:
['1 baguette' '4 ounces bar bittersweet chocolate, cut into 16 pieces'
 '1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil' 'Coarse sea salt, for sprinkling']
instructions:

title: Sole Steamed with Tomato-Leek Sauce
ingredients:
['1 tablespoon olive oil' '1 cup leeks, chopped'
 '1/2 teaspoon minced garlic' '1/2 cup dry white wine'
 '3 tomatoes, chopped' '1 cup chicken broth' '1/2 teaspoon dried thyme'
 '1 teaspoon dried dill weed' '2 fillets sole']

 'Lay the sole filets on top of the vegetables, and cover the skillet.'
 'Cook until the fish is opaque, and flakes easily with a fork, about 10 minutes.'
 'Ladle the sauce over the sole to serve.']

title: Healthy Bison Chili
ingredients:
['2 teaspoons vegetable oil' '2 pounds lean ground bison'
 '3 poblano peppers, seeded and diced' '2 medium onions, diced'
 '6 tablespoons mexican chili powder' '1 teaspoon ground coriander'
 '1 teaspoon ground cumin' '1 teaspoon kosher salt'
 '1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper' '3 cloves garlic, minced'
 'One 14.5-ounce can whole fire-roasted tomatoes, crushed by hand'
 'One 15.5-ounce can black beans, drained and rinsed'
 'One 15.5-ounce can red kidney beans, drained and rinsed'
 'One 15.5-ounce can white hominy, drained and rinsed'
 'One 8-ounce container low-fat sour cream, optional'
 '1/2 cup shredded low-fat cheese, optional'
 '1/2 cup fresh cilantro leaves, optional'
 '1/2 medium red onion, finely chopped, optional'
 'Lime wedges, for serving, optional'
 'Avocado, diced, for serving, optional']
instructions:
['Heat 1 teaspoon of the oil in a large soup pot or dutch oven over medium-high heat.'
 'When the oil shimmers, add the bison and cook until browned, taking care not to break the meat into very small pieces, about 10 minutes.'
 'Transfer the bison to a plate using a slotted spoon and set aside.'
 'Drain the liquid in the bottom of the pot and discard.'
 'Keep the pot over medium-high heat and add the remaining 1 teaspoon oil, the poblano peppers and onions.'
 'Cook until softened and beginning to brown, about 5 minutes.'
 'Add the chili powder, coriander, cumin, salt, cayenne pepper and garlic.'
 'Cook and stir until the spices are fragrant and toasted, 1 to 2 minutes.'
 'Add the tomatoes with the juices, and bring to a simmer while scraping any browned bits off the bottom of the pan, about 2 minutes.'
 'Return the bison to the pot and add the black beans, kidney beans, hominy and 4 cups water.'
 'Bring to a boil, and then reduce the heat, cover and simmer until thickened, about 45 minutes.'
 'Season with salt.'
 'Serve with the sour cream, cheese, cilantro, onions, lime and avocados, if desired.'
 'Per serving : calories 494; total fat 15.5 grams; saturated fat 5 grams; protein 43 grams; total carbohydrate 52 grams; sugar: 7 grams; fiber 18 grams; cholesterol 83 milligrams; sodium 1031 milligrams']

 '1 teaspoon baking powder']

 'And return them to the baking sheets.'

 'Remove from baking sheets to cool on wire racks.'
 'These cookies can be stored for a month in an airtight container.']

text: <TITLE_START> Fried Chicken<TITLE_END><INGR_START> 4 pieces chicken breast<INGR_NEXT> 6 pieces chicken leg<INGR_NEXT> 6 pieces chicken wings<INGR_NEXT> 2 pints buttermilk<INGR_NEXT> 4 cloves garlic<INGR_NEXT> 4 teaspoons hot sauce<INGR_NEXT> 4 cups canola oil<INGR_NEXT> 1/4 cups butter<INGR_NEXT> 4 cups flour<INGR_NEXT> 4 tablespoons kosher sea salt<INGR_NEXT> 2 tablespoons pepper<INGR_NEXT> 1 tablespoon poultry seasoning<INGR_END><INSTR_START> marinate cleaned chicken pieces in buttermilk, garlic and hot pepper sauce for at least 2 hours and up to 48 hours before frying.<INSTR_NEXT> i use an electric skillet, heating oil and butter to 375 degrees.<INSTR_NEXT> test the oil to make sure its hot.<INSTR_NEXT> mix flour and seasonings in a large shallow pan.<INSTR_NEXT> take the chicken from the buttermilk and dredge in flour; mix, shake off excess flour.<INSTR_NEXT> fry for 20 minutes on one side, then turn at least 1 or 2 times until done.<INSTR_NEXT> drain on paper towels and dig in!<INSTR_NEXT> if you want gravy, then drain off the oil leaving a couple tablespoons in the skillet.<INSTR_NEXT> add approximately 1/8 cup of the flour mixture to the oil in the skillet and brown the roux until it is a nice brown color.<INSTR_NEXT> mix whole milk and chicken stock in a measuring cup to measure about 1/2 to 2 cups of liquid.<INSTR_NEXT> add slowly to the roux in the skillet, whisking in to remove lumps.<INSTR_NEXT> heat through, and ladle over mashed potatoes!<INSTR_END>
title: Fried Chicken
ingredients:
['4 pieces chicken breast' '6 pieces chicken leg' '6 pieces chicken wings'
 '2 pints buttermilk' '4 cloves garlic' '4 teaspoons hot sauce'
 '4 cups canola oil' '1/4 cups butter' '4 cups flour'
 '4 tablespoons kosher sea salt' '2 tablespoons pepper'
 '1 tablespoon poultry seasoning']
instructions:
['Marinate cleaned chicken pieces in buttermilk, garlic and hot pepper sauce for at least 2 hours and up to 48 hours before frying.'
 'I use an electric skillet, heating oil and butter to 375 degrees.'
 'Test the oil to make sure its hot.'
 'Mix flour and seasonings in a large shallow pan.'
 'Take the chicken from the buttermilk and dredge in flour; mix, shake off excess flour.'
 'Fry for 20 minutes on one side, then turn at least 1 or 2 times until done.'
 'Drain on paper towels and dig in!'
 'If you want gravy, then drain off the oil leaving a couple tablespoons in the skillet.'
 'Add approximately 1/8 cup of the flour mixture to the oil in the skillet and brown the roux until it is a nice brown color.'
 'Mix whole milk and chicken stock in a measuring cup to measure about 1/2 to 2 cups of liquid.'
 'Add slowly to the roux in the skillet, whisking in to remove lumps.'
 'Heat through, and ladle over mashed potatoes!']

title: Curry Citrus Chicken

['4 boneless skinless chicken thighs'
 '2 tablespoons onions, finely chopped' '2 tablespoons lemon juice'

 '12 teaspoon curry powder' '12 teaspoon ground cumin'

 '1 tablespoon water']

title: Vickys Creamy Yellow Pea and Ham Soup, Gluten, Dairy, Egg & Soy-Free

 '200 grams rindless diced bacon + another 50g rinsed well'

 '3 finely diced spring onion/scallions' '1 pinch black pepper to taste']

text: <TITLE_START> Spaghetti Squash with Marinara<TITLE_END><INGR_START> 2 whole spaghetti squash<INGR_NEXT> 1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil<INGR_NEXT> gray salt and freshly ground black pepper<INGR_NEXT> 4 cups prepared marinara sauce<INGR_END><INSTR_START> preheat the oven to 450 degrees f.<INSTR_NEXT> split the squashes in half and scrape out seeds.<INSTR_NEXT> line an oven tray with aluminum foil.<INSTR_NEXT> season the spaghetti squash with olive oil, salt, and pepper.<INSTR_NEXT> place flesh side down and roast for 30 to 40 minutes until fully cooked.<INSTR_NEXT> remove from the oven and let rest until cool enough to handle.<INSTR_NEXT> meanwhile heat the marinara sauce in a large saute pan.<INSTR_NEXT> when squash is cool enough to handle, using a large kitchen spoon scrape the strands of squash from the inside of the skin.<INSTR_NEXT> toss the spaghetti squash in the pan with the hot marinara for just long enough to get hot.<INSTR_NEXT> serve and enjoy.<INSTR_END>
title: Spaghetti Squash with Marinara
ingredients:
['2 whole spaghetti squash' '1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil'
 'Gray salt and freshly ground black pepper'
 '4 cups prepared marinara sauce']
instructions:
['Preheat the oven to 450 degrees f.'
 'Split the squashes in half and scrape out seeds.'
 'Line an oven tray with aluminum foil.'
 'Season the spaghetti squash with olive oil, salt, and pepper.'
 'Place flesh side down and roast for 30 to 40 minutes until fully cooked.'

 'Let cool and add the other blueberries.'

title: Carrot Muffins on a Grid
ingredients:
['14 cup moist plump currants' '23 cup grated carrot, lightly packed'
 '13 cup pecans, finely chopped'
 '13 cup shredded coconut, preferably unsweetened'
 '4 tablespoons unsalted butter' '1 12 cups all-purpose flour'
 '1 tablespoon double-acting baking powder' '1 pinch salt'
 '34 teaspoon ground cinnamon' '14 teaspoon ground ginger' '13 cup sugar'
 '1 12 cups milk' '2 large eggs' '1 teaspoon vanilla extract'
 'Warm maple syrup']
instructions:
['*if your currants are not moist and plump, place them in a heatproof bowl and pour boiling water over them; let steep for a minute, drain, turn out onto a paper towel and pat them dry; set aside.'
 'Toss together the carrots, pecans, coconut, and currants in a bowl; set aside.'
 'Preheat a waffle iron.' 'Melt butter and reserve.'
 'In a bowl, whisk the flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, ginger, and sugar together.'
 'In another bowl, beat the milk, eggs, and vanilla together using a whisk.'
 'Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients; whisk until just combined.'
 'Stir in the carrot mixture; then mix in the melted butter.'
 'Lightly butter or spray the grids of the waffle iron; if needed, brush or spray the grids again only is subsequent waffles stick.'
 'Spoon about 1 cup batter onto the grids.'
 'Use a metal spatula or wooden spoon to spread the batter almost to the edge.'
 'Close the lid and bake until browned and lightly crisped.'
 'Carefully turn the waffle over, turning it top to bottom and front to back, and continue to bake 1 minute or longer.'
 '*before measuring out the batter for each new waffle, stir to redistribute the ingredients.'
 'Top with warmed maple syrup or honey.']

title: Almond Butter Cookies
ingredients:
['1 cup butter, softened' '34 cup sugar' '1 teaspoon almond extract'
 '2 cups all-purpose flour' '12 teaspoon baking powder' '14 teaspoon salt'
 '12 cup real semi-sweet chocolate chips' '2 teaspoons shortening']

['Heat oven to 400f combine butter, sugar and almond extract in large bowl.'
 'Beat at medium speed, until creamy.'
 'Reduce speed to low and add all remaining cookie ingredients.'
 'Beat until well mixed.'
 'Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into 1-inch balls.'
 'Place 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.'
 'Flatten balls to 1/4 inch thick with bottom of buttered glass dipped in sugar.'
 'Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.'
 'Melt chocolate chips and shortening over low heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth .'
 'Drizzle or pipe chocolate on cookies making a christmas tree design, if desired.'
 'Tip: bake a variety of cookies using the same dough by rolling balls in decorator sugars or pressing halved red or green candied cherries onto cookies or rolling balls in finely chopped nuts before baking.']

text: <TITLE_START> Endive and Fennel Salad With Mint and Orange-Blossom Dressing<TITLE_END><INGR_START> 4 endives, a mixture of green and red<INGR_NEXT> 2 fennel bulbs<INGR_NEXT> 1 bunch mint leaf, picked from stems<INGR_NEXT> 2 garlic cloves, peeled<INGR_NEXT> 4 tablespoons olive oil<INGR_NEXT> 2 tablespoons lemon juice<INGR_NEXT> 1 tablespoon lime juice<INGR_NEXT> 1 teaspoon runny pale honey<INGR_NEXT> 1 teaspoon orange blossom water<INGR_NEXT> salt and pepper<INGR_END><INSTR_START> slice an inch off the stem of the endives and the outer leaves will fall away.<INSTR_NEXT> peel away the others until just the cores are left.<INSTR_NEXT> slice the cores into quarters.<INSTR_NEXT> rinse the leaves, then pat them dry and place in a large bowl.<INSTR_NEXT> cut the fennel bulbs in half and slice into semicircular slivers, right up to and including the fluffy green part.<INSTR_NEXT> add to the endives, along with the mint leaves.<INSTR_NEXT> for the dressing, pound the garlic using a pestle and mortar until it starts to break down.<INSTR_NEXT> slowly add the olive oil and stir with the pestle, then add the lemon and lime juice.<INSTR_NEXT> the ratio of lemon to oil is a personal preference, so experiment.<INSTR_NEXT> next, add the honey and orange-blossom water, and season.<INSTR_NEXT> toss into the salad just before serving.<INSTR_END>
title: Endive and Fennel Salad With Mint and Orange-Blossom Dressing
ingredients:
['4 endives, a mixture of green and red' '2 fennel bulbs'
 '1 bunch mint leaf, picked from stems' '2 garlic cloves, peeled'
 '4 tablespoons olive oil' '2 tablespoons lemon juice'
 '1 tablespoon lime juice' '1 teaspoon runny pale honey'
 '1 teaspoon orange blossom water' 'Salt and pepper']
instructions:
['Slice an inch off the stem of the endives and the outer leaves will fall away.'
 'Peel away the others until just the cores are left.'
 'Slice the cores into quarters.'
 'Rinse the leaves, then pat them dry and place in a large bowl.'
 'Cut the fennel bulbs in half and slice into semicircular slivers, right up to and including the fluffy green part.'
 'Add to the endives, along with the mint leaves.'
 'For the dressing, pound the garlic using a pestle and mortar until it starts to break down.'
 'Slowly add the olive oil and stir with the pestle, then add the lemon and lime juice.'
 'The ratio of lemon to oil is a personal preference, so experiment.'
 'Next, add the honey and orange-blossom water, and season.'
 'Toss into the salad just before serving.']
instructions_v1:
['Slowly add the olive oil and stir with the pestle, then add the lemon and lime juice.'
 'Rinse the leaves, then pat them dry and place in a large bowl.'
 'Slice the cores into quarters.'

title: Smoked-Duck Salad with Walnuts and Raspberries
ingredients:
['1/2 pound smoked duck breastskin and fat removed and reserved, breast thinly sliced crosswise'

 'Add the frisee, boston lettuce and walnuts and toss to coat.'

title: Simple Sweet Potatoes
ingredients:
['3 large sweet potatoes' '2 avocados, peeled and pitted'
 '1/4 teaspoon salt' '1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper'
 '1/3 cup diced red onion' '2 tablespoons unsalted butter, divided']
instructions:
['Preheat oven to 450 degrees f .'
 'Make a long, narrow cut lengthwise down the center of each sweet potato.'
 'Wrap each potato in aluminum foil.'
 'Bake potatoes directly on the rack of the preheated oven until tender, about 1 hour.'
 'Mash avocado flesh, salt, and pepper together in a bowl with a fork until mostly smooth.'
 'Fold onion into avocado mixture.'
 'Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate until chilled, about 45 minutes.'
 'Remove potatoes from foil and slice open, pushing the two ends of each together to open the potato.'
 'Divide 1/2 of the butter between the potato openings.'
 'Spoon avocado mixture into each potato and top each with remaining butter.']

text: <TITLE_START> Kuwaiti Curried Chicken (Quwarmah Ala Dajaj)<TITLE_END><INGR_START> 3 lbs chicken, skinned and jointed<INGR_NEXT> salt<INGR_NEXT> 1 34 teaspoons baharat mixed spice<INGR_NEXT> 1 teaspoon turmeric<INGR_NEXT> 14 cup olive oil<INGR_NEXT> 2 large onions, chopped<INGR_NEXT> 2 garlic cloves, crushed<INGR_NEXT> 1 teaspoon fresh ginger, grated<INGR_NEXT> 1 stick cinnamon bark<INGR_NEXT> 1 cup tomato sauce<INGR_NEXT> 14 cup water<INGR_NEXT> 2 dried limes<INGR_NEXT> 1 cup frozen okra<INGR_END><INSTR_START> rinse and wipe chicken pieces dry and sprinkle with salt.<INSTR_NEXT> combine baharat and turmeric and rub half onto chicken pieces.<INSTR_NEXT> leave for 15 minutes.<INSTR_NEXT> heat olive oil and brown chicken pieces on each side.<INSTR_NEXT> remove to plate.<INSTR_NEXT> add onion and fry gently until transparent.<INSTR_NEXT> add garlic, ginger, remaining spice mixture, and cinnamon bark to the onion and fry for 5 minutes stirring often.<INSTR_NEXT> add tomato sauce, water, salt to taste, and loomi pierced twice with a skewer or loomi powder.<INSTR_NEXT> bring to a high simmer.<INSTR_NEXT> add chicken pieces and okra if using, reduce heat to low and simmer very gently for 1 1/2 hours until chicken is tender and sauce is thick.<INSTR_NEXT> serve hot with recipe #79179 or other basmati rice dish and salad.<INSTR_END>
title: Kuwaiti Curried Chicken (Quwarmah Ala Dajaj)
ingredients:
['3 lbs chicken, skinned and jointed' 'Salt'
 '1 34 teaspoons baharat mixed spice' '1 teaspoon turmeric'
 '14 cup olive oil' '2 large onions, chopped' '2 garlic cloves, crushed'
 '1 teaspoon fresh ginger, grated' '1 stick cinnamon bark'
 '1 cup tomato sauce' '14 cup water' '2 dried limes' '1 cup frozen okra']
instructions:
['Rinse and wipe chicken pieces dry and sprinkle with salt.'
 'Combine baharat and turmeric and rub half onto chicken pieces.'
 'Leave for 15 minutes.'
 'Heat olive oil and brown chicken pieces on each side.'
 'Remove to plate.' 'Add onion and fry gently until transparent.'
 'Add garlic, ginger, remaining spice mixture, and cinnamon bark to the onion and fry for 5 minutes stirring often.'
 'Add tomato sauce, water, salt to taste, and loomi pierced twice with a skewer or loomi powder.'
 'Bring to a high simmer.'
 'Add chicken pieces and okra if using, reduce heat to low and simmer very gently for 1 1/2 hours until chicken is tender and sauce is thick.'
 'Serve hot with recipe #79179 or other basmati rice dish and salad.']

title: Veggie Chips
ingredients:

 'Salt to taste' 'Soybean oil']

title: Warm Chickpea Salad With Ginger

 '2 garlic cloves, crushed' '2 cans chickpeas, drained & rinsed'

 'Sprinkle the cumin and paprika on top, gently stir then serve warm.']
